Name: Deanna Wilkinson
Description:
Deanna and [Shawn "Junior" Keegan](https://tdor.translivesmatter.info/reports/1996/05/20/shawn-junior-keegan_toronto-ontario-canada_64bcd821) were both shot in the back of the head with a .357 magnum filled with hollow-point bullets by Marcello Palma.

> Marcello Palma, who hunted down and shot three prostitutes during a one-night killing spree that terrorized Toronto in May of 1996, was convicted yesterday of first-degree murder and imprisoned for life.
> 
> The married air-conditioning installer lost his five-year bid to be excused of criminal responsibility for the point-blank shootings on grounds of mental illness.
> 
> Mr. Palma, 34, nodded his head slightly and his eyes filled with tears when Mr. Justice David Watt of the Ontario Superior Court dismissed his alleged psychiatric symptoms as fake and declared that the killings were planned and deliberate executions.
> 
> Mr. Palma, he found, was motivated by rage over rejections by his wife and his mistress and took it out on a class of people he loathed and considered "scum" even though he was a frequent customer.

Name: R. D. Neadeau
Description:
R. was beaten to death in a condemned building. She died as a result of blows to the head and abdomen.

> A 38-year-old [woman] who Minneapolis police say was a [trans woman] with a record of [sex work] was found beaten to death early Friday in an apartment of a condemned building at 14 E. Franklin Av.
>
> The body of [deadname] D. Neadeau, 38, of Minneapolis, was found by a friend about 1 a.m. Authorities said [she] had been killed shortly before [her] body was found. The Hennepin County medical examiner's office said Neadeau suffered injuries from blows to the head and abdomen.
>
> No one has been arrested in the slaying.
